FEMSA: The Most Interesting Company in Mexico
A Post Market [https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFUMtuhSAQ_ZrL0vBQLy5YdNN=
dk_6BAZkqVcDAqPHvi7poMslk5uTkPAaNMMZ0qjVmJFuG1DurWMulaOqOWFVbJhtJXO5_EoDXbl=
GYNiDrZhY3aHQx3AxKeUMmJaUVmg8S3obqujamBS1qyQSXknWdIJdOrzfrIAygYId0xgBkURPim=
l_i48U_y-DhECFVQ_Tl-r5IXzrNgMQpTjlljAsmmpaKilW7Ofh-jsH_-ldN_cirvJmMepgvPkkq=
RDQxuTAWeJ60h-UGSoa-bL8Fh2cPQZsF7BMPn0Jut3iuoAIceYHL0_O8MndCyHfbkqJmY6km_Av=
9AW0Sdko] x Not Boring [https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFUMuOhSAM_ZrL0v=
AQHwsWs5ndfIMBqV7mChioGv9-UBeTNGna0-Y8Ro0wx3SqNWYkW4Y0OKtYwzsh655YVVvWyY64P=
EwJwGu3KEwbkHUzixs1uhjuD0q5JG8lWa9lb1rZagE9bXTbjLK1vemmlteTJRfPoDfrIIygYId0=
xgBkUW_ENb_E14t_l8LDIUKqxujLtOrxc_4QpzjllDEumJANFRWrdnPw_ZyD__WvmvqZV3kzGcv=
99UqSChFNTC7MBf68tYflBor8oXS_BYfnAEGbBezjDJ8sbqF4rqACHHmBS86zvOz2QnRt05DCZm=
NJJfwT_QEtmHSL] Collaboration=20
The C-Store Internet
In Mexico, the road to the Metaverse goes through a convenience store.=C2=
=A0
Fourteen million Mexican shoppers walk through OXXO=E2=80=99s doors each da=
y to buy everything from a Coca-Cola to Fortnite V-Bucks.=C2=A0
OXXO is the on-ramp for the digital economy in Mexico. Over 60% of Mexico=
=E2=80=99s population is unbanked, and the Mexican economy is still largely=
 cash-based. Instead of entering a credit card online, millions of shoppers=
 go to the nearest OXXO to pay cash for over 5,000 digital services, from V=
-Bucks to Amazon to Netflix to electricity bills. Mexican consumers trust O=
XXO more than they trust the banks, as evidenced by the fact that OXXO=E2=
=80=99s Saldazo debit card [https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFUMuOwyAM_J=
pySxQgrx449LK_EZngpLQEInCaZr9-SXtYydLIM7JHMyMQziEeag2J2JYwDtYo3opeNvWVGVUb3=
jc9s2mYIuIC1imKG7J1086OQDb4z0VViYbdFfKm6_oaRMcNCDRTW0ONpodRTNfecHb6DLAZi35E=
hS-MR_DInLoTrekibxfxk2ff9zK836Ecw5JX7cKc4WQKjR4nO9qQCoMFQXwgQZHAGfgNzCpRiYp=
zIbls2kqWvHzpXbyO2S-P5VJXyyzKtOlEMD7P7ywqH0iHaP2c5ecdFnQfIUccMi6bt3QM6EE7NN=
_09O3rE4aOFZXHPTkkwvglz0quUvZd27LsZkJuzv8b_QFuyoJs] is already the most pop=
ular in the country. That puts OXXO in the prime position to build the digi=
tal wallet for Mexico.=C2=A0
To a reader in a developed country, the idea that a convenience store (=E2=
=80=9Cc-store=E2=80=9D) chain could become a fintech powerhouse sounds prep=
osterous. It sounds even more loco when you learn that OXXO=E2=80=99s paren=
t company, Fomento Econ=C3=B3mico Mexicano, S.A.B. de C.V. (FEMSA), is the =
130-year-old descendent of a brewery, Cervecer=C3=ADa Cuauht=C3=A9moc Mocte=
zuma, founded by five families in Monterrey in 1890. But emerging markets a=
fford opportunities for scope unrivaled in developed markets. When a countr=
y=E2=80=99s infrastructure is underdeveloped, the companies that build out =
the physical and digital logistics and distribution own unimpeachable chann=
els through which they can push a wide range of products and services.=C2=
=A0
Digitally, WeChat, Gojek, Grab, and other Super Apps are essentially the in=
ternet in their respective home countries. Because they own the digital inf=
rastructure, they=E2=80=99re able to build their own services on top or ext=
ract rent from the companies that do. FEMSA falls into a related category o=
f companies that, by owning the customer relationship and habits due to phy=
sical proximity, may be able to expand into ownership of their digital tran=
sactions as well.=C2=A0
If it succeeds, FEMSA will be Mexico=E2=80=99s Super App.=C2=A0
FEMSA is to Mexico as Reliance [https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxVUMuKwz=
AM_Jr61uBX0vTgQy_7G8Gx5dRbP4KtpOTv121hlwUJgYbRaMZohCWXQ625ItkqlMlbxQY-il5ei=
VXSsrEfia-TKwBR-6CwbEDWbQ7eaPQ5vRmU8p7cleydmM3FAZMDcxQkFRdztdZJrkE4R146k96s=
h2RAwQ7lyAlIUHfEtZ7E7cS_WqWMcy4-LV3d5oraPDqTYwPW1gWC141-Xtr3T32cszv7ZL0mXnH=
KKWNcMNEPVHSs2-cn348lxe94kjQu_N9FUtSvVIMfdx0hvIFmcGozbsnjMUHScwD78Y6ftN5W8F=
hBJXjWAIhQPstXIFchxsswkKZmc8st_Qn9AI3fgb0] is to India. Both are old compan=
ies, run by descendents of the founders, with histories of vertical integra=
tion and unmatched capabilities in distribution in economies that lack stro=
ng infrastructure, and a proven ability to push a variety of products throu=
gh those distribution channels.=C2=A0
Where Reliance dominated polyester, petrochemicals, and refining in India, =
FEMSA built its empire on cerveza and Coca-Cola. When he took the reins of =
the family business, Reliance=E2=80=99s Mukesh Ambani=E2=80=99s first new v=
enture was to launch Reliance Retail, which is now the largest retailer by =
stores in India. FEMSA=E2=80=99s Chairman and former CEO, Jose Antonio =E2=
=80=9CDevil Fern=C3=A1ndez=E2=80=9D Carbajal, took over his family company=
=E2=80=99s struggling OXXO subsidiary and grew it into the largest convenie=
nce store chain by number of stores in the Americas. And now, like Reliance=
 did with Jio, FEMSA is using its legacy assets, and the cash flow they spi=
t off, to build a digital growth engine that might transform the business, =
and the economy in its home country, yet again.=C2=A0
Today, FEMSA=E2=80=99s value comes from three main businesses: a 47% stake =
in the world=E2=80=99s largest Coca-Cola bottler, a 15% stake in brewer Hei=
neken, and FEMSA Comercio, which runs pharmacies, gas stations, and most im=
portantly, OXXO convenience stores throughout Mexico and Latin America.=C2=
=A0
Funds love c-stores. They=E2=80=99re the closest thing the physical world h=
as to the internet. They=E2=80=99re easy to stand up, ubiquitous, offer hig=
h returns on capital, sell high-margin products like soft drinks, alcohol, =
salty snacks, and tobacco, and generate strong brand loyalty by becoming a =
part of their customers=E2=80=99 daily routine. I start every morning with =
Wawa, and until Amazon delivers $1 coffee within five minutes, that=E2=80=
=99s not going to change.=C2=A0
With COVID though, that physical ubiquity, typically a massive moat, became=
 a liability. Mexico has been one of the hardest hit countries in the world=
, with mortality rates near 10%, and the government has enacted austerity m=
easures instead of stimulus. While the country has largely avoided lockdown=
s, many people have opted to stay home, and same store sales across FEMSA=
=E2=80=99s properties have taken a hit.=C2=A0
As a result, FEMSA (NYSE: FMX) crashed from a pre-COVID high of $97.59 all =
the way to $53.50 in early November, before picking up after Biden=E2=80=99=
s victory (he=E2=80=99s expected to be friendlier to Mexico) and promising =
vaccine developments positioned FEMSA as a reopening trade.=C2=A0
Even after its recent move up, FEMSA=E2=80=99s core business is still under=
valued and comes with a free option on Mexico=E2=80=99s Super App. Today, F=
EMSA is like 7-11, the Post Office, Coca-Cola, and Heineken all rolled into=
 one. Tomorrow, if it=E2=80=99s able to fight through the COVID dip and acc=
elerate its digital transformation, it could be all that plus M-Pesa or Goj=
ek.=C2=A0
It will have to act quickly to make that happen. The Latin American digital=
 wallet is a highly sought after prize, and COVID has handed digital-first =
competitors a drawbridge over its physical moat.=C2=A0
This isn=E2=80=99t FEMSA=E2=80=99s first rodeo, though. Devil Fern=C3=A1nde=
z told a Stanford GSB class [https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFULtuhDAQ_=
BpcImwDhsLF5UGkJEWqpETGbMA5YyM_IPx9zF0RaaXVzOxqNCNFgMm6g6_WBxQ9uF6NHNekoVXZ=
opGXI26qBinffzuARSjNg4uA1jhoJUVQ1tw-ioJUaOaUAB1EKSljDMsSiqGuCGlZk2DJmhadPr2=
IowIjgcMG7rAGkOZzCKvP6CUjXZp93_PDxhAHyKVdTkYEOWe02zL69Pbx9fJq2GetZUZqZUb4TS=
wmNCGtfEjg4716xOUDZdWFdaR7vqQMnBSkwOkM06ouaI7zbdjJdkxm-Vmyslgmkvs4-CDk9XRFj=
hsbBuuUmZJ8ncUC-iak9H3aSzQqHD0YMWgY78WEe5W3nOFYgRvYvYYQwN3Js62W0obVNUpuo02l=
mn-jPxeRhTs] in 2009:=C2=A0
Mexico has been a typical emerging country with all the typical problems th=
at they have, which is every period of time, we have some kind of political=
 or economic crisis. This (the financial crisis) is the first time the econ=
omic crisis wasn=E2=80=99t created by Mexicans!
COVID is the second. Each time FEMSA has faced disaster in its 130 year his=
tory -- from devaluation to financial crisis to murder -- it has reset and =
come back stronger.
We are just getting started. Keep reading online for the whole story, the b=
